### Intuition

Before explaining the solution, I will write how I came up with the solution.

The main point to notice in this problem is that the moment we get an invalid parenthesis, the subarray can't start from beyond this point.
Not clear ? Let's understand with an example.

Consider this simple string.
```()()))()(())```, at index 4 the subarray starting from index 0 becomes invalid, it is clear the longest valid parenthesis won't start from [0, 3] and end after 4.

This striked me that I can use a sliding window to solve this problem.

### How to solve ?

Consider a window with left end shown by **i** and right end shown by **j**.
Initially **i = 0 and j = 0**
Let us consider another variable k which will help us to determine when subarray becomes invalid.

Now, we start moving j keeping i as fixed. 

Increment k when we encounter ```(``` and decrement when we encounter ```)```.

Whenever k becomes zero we will update our answer with max(ans,  j - i + 1)
It is clear when k becomes negative the subarray will become invalid, so we will move the left end i.e **i** to the new position.

**Question**
Why are we updating the answer when k is 0 and not when k > 0.
**Answer**
We know for sure, whenever we get k as 0 the subarray is valid and length will be j - i + 1.
But when k > 0 the subarray is still valid, but the length will be less than j - i + 1.
But ofcourse we are missing some values, since the length which is less j - i + 1 can be a better answer.

Consider this string ```(()```. Here, we will never get k = 0 and hence we can't update our answer.

**How to resolve this?**
We have to repeat the above process but this time starting i = n - 1 and j = n - 1. Now, keep moving j to the left side and do the same as above. Here k will increase when we encounter ```)``` and decrease when we encounter ```(```.

### Cpp Code

```
class Solution {
public:
    int longestValidParentheses(string s) {
        int n = s.length(), i = 0, ans = 0, k = 0;
        for(int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
            if(s[j] == '(')  k++;
            else if(s[j] == ')') {
                k--;
                if(k == 0)
                    ans = max(ans, j - i + 1);
            }
            if(k < 0) {
                k = 0;
                i = j + 1;
            }
        }
        k = 0, i = n - 1;
        for(int j = n - 1; j >= 0; j--) {
            if(s[j] == ')') {
                k++;
            }
            else if(s[j] == '(') {
                k--;
                if(k == 0)
                    ans = max(ans, i - j + 1);
            }
            if(k < 0) {
                k = 0;
                i = j - 1;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

