* `prev` stores the index, after which the valid subtring can be found.

* if a closing bracket `)` is found without it's previous opening bracket, then we update the `prev` to this index, as the previous valid parenthesis cannot extended through this index.

```
class Solution {
public:
    int longestValidParentheses(string s) {
        stack<int> st ;
        int ans = 0 , prev = -1 ;

        for(int i = prev + 1 ; i < s.size() ; ++i ){
            if(s[i] == '(') st.push(i) ;
            else{
                if(st.empty()) {prev = i ;continue ;}
                st.pop() ;
                //now update the answer 
                if(st.size()) ans = max(ans,i-st.top()) ;
                else ans = max(ans,i - prev) ;
            }
        }

        return ans ;
    }
};
```

