solutions.content:
Calculate and maintain 2 DP states: 

 1. pal[i][j] , which is whether s[i..j] forms a pal

 2.  d[i], which
        is the minCut for s[i..n-1]

Once we comes to a pal[i][j]==true:

 - if j==n-1, the string s[i..n-1] is a Pal, minCut is 0, d[i]=0; 
 - else: the current cut num (first cut s[i..j] and then cut the rest
   s[j+1...n-1]) is 1+d[j+1], compare it to the exisiting minCut num
   d[i], repalce if smaller.

d[0] is the answer.

     class Solution {
        public:
            int minCut(string s) {
                if(s.empty()) return 0;
                int n = s.size();
                vector<vector<bool>> pal(n,vector<bool>(n,false));
                vector<int> d(n);
                for(int i=n-1;i>=0;i--)
                {
                    d[i]=n-i-1;
                    for(int j=i;j<n;j++)
                    {
                        if(s[i]==s[j] && (j-i<2 || pal[i+1][j-1]))
                        {
                           pal[i][j]=true;
                           if(j==n-1)
                               d[i]=0;
                           else if(d[j+1]+1<d[i])
                               d[i]=d[j+1]+1;
                        }
                    }
                }
                return d[0];
            }
        };

