# 1. Recursive Code [TLE]
#### Approach
- We will be using the naive recursive approach on the same line as **MCM DP**.
- Will be using front **partition DP**.

#### Complexity
- Time complexity: **~ O(2^n), Highly Exponential**

- Space complexity: **O(n)**
```
class Solution {
    private static boolean isPalindrome(int i, int j, String s){
        while(i<j){
            if(s.charAt(i)!=s.charAt(j)) return false;
            i++;
            j--;
        }
        return true;
    }

    private static int fun(int cut, String s){
        // Base Case 
        if(cut==s.length()) return 0;

        // Code 
        int minCuts = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        for(int partition=cut;partition<s.length();partition++){
            if(isPalindrome(cut,partition,s)){
                int cuts = 1 + fun(partition+1,s);
                minCuts = Math.min(minCuts,cuts);
            }
        }
        return minCuts;
    }

    public int minCut(String s){
        return fun(0,s)-1;
    }
}
// Recursive Code 
// Time Complexity : ~ O(2^n), Highly Exponential
// Space Complexity : O(n)

// s = "aabb"
// s = "a"|"a"|"b"|"b" -> 3 cuts -> so we can say that for every input answer will always exist 
// s = "aa"|"b"|"b" -> 2 cuts
// s = "a"|"a"|"bb" -> 2 cuts
// s = "aa"|"bb" -> 1 cuts (min)

// So to find the min number of cuts needed so that every substring will result in a palindrome 
// We will use the approach of "Front Partitions"
// s = "aabb"
// s = "a"|"abb"
// 1. 1 + "a"|"a"|"bb" + 1 + "aa"|"bb"
```
