# 3. Tabulation Code [TLE]
#### Approach
- Tabulating the code, in a hope to remove the continous TLE encountered.
- But finally we came to know that just optimizing the DP will not work, we have to come up with some other optimization in the time complexity of the code.
- Then we observed that we are actually doing the isPalindrome calculation again and again for every other substring we formed but we should observe that it can have many overlapping subproblems which can be memoized in order to optimize the time complexity of the code .

#### Complexity
- Time complexity: **~ O(n * n * n), Linear Complexity**

- Space complexity: **O(n + n)**
```
class Solution {
    private static boolean isPalindrome(int i, int j, String s){
        while(i<=j){
            if(s.charAt(i)!=s.charAt(j)) return false;
            i++;
            j--;
        }
        return true;
    }

    private static int fun(String s){
        int len = s.length();
        int[] dp = new int[len+1];
        dp[len] = 0;
        for(int cut=len-1;cut>=0;cut--){
            int minCuts = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
            for(int partition=cut;partition<len;partition++){
                if(isPalindrome(cut,partition,s)){
                    int cuts = 1 + dp[partition+1];
                    minCuts = Math.min(minCuts,cuts);
                }
            }
            dp[cut] = minCuts;
        }
        return dp[0]-1;
    }

    public int minCut(String s){
        return fun(s);
    }
}
// Tabulation Code 
// Time Complexity : ~ O(n * n * n), Linear Complexity
// Space Complexity : O(n + n)

```
