solutions.content:
	Step 1: 
	      Create a 2D bool array dp[n][n] where dp[i][j] indicates whether substring [i...j] is a palindrome. 
		  Create an array minCuts[n + 1] which saves the min cuts for the substring [0...n - 1]. 

	      Base case:  - A character is considered a palindrome. 
                        => dp[i][i] = true for i in range [0, n)
                      - Maximum cuts required for the substring [0...i - 1] is i - 1. 
                    where the string is cut into one-letter substring.
                        => minCuts[i] = i - 1 for i in range [0, n]

    Step 2: Handle the case for substring [i...j]:
	      If s[i] == s[j]:
		       if the substring is smaller or equal to 2 elements: (j - i) <= 2
		       If the substring [i + 1... j - 1] is a palindrome.
                 => The substring [i...j] is a palindrome => dp[i][j] = true.
                 => Recalculate minimum cuts for substring [0...j].
						Minimum cuts for substring [0...j] is whether:
						+ The minimum cuts for substring [0...i] + 1 
						+ The minimum cuts for substring [0...j]
						=> minCuts[j + 1] = min(minCuts[j + 1], minCuts[i] + 1)  
```
int minCuts(string &str)
{
    int size = str.size();
    int dp[size][size];
    int minCuts[size + 1];
    memset(dp, 0, sizeof(dp);
    memset(minCuts, 0, sizeof(minCuts));
    for (int i = 0; i <= size; ++i)
    {
        minCuts[i] = i - 1;
        if (i < size)
           dp[i][i] = true;
    }
    for (int j = 1; j < size; ++j)
    {
        for (int i = j; i >= 0; --i)
        {
            if (str[i] == str[j] and (j - i <= 2 or dp[i + 1][j - 1]))
            {
                dp[i][j] = true;
                minCuts[j + 1] = min(minCuts[j + 1], minCuts[i] + 1);
            }
        }
    }
    return minCuts[size];
}
```

