class Solution {
public:
    int minCut(string s) {
        int N = s.size();
        vector<bool> ispalin(N+1,false);
        vector<int> dp(N+1,0x7fffffff);
        dp[0] = -1;
        for(int i = 1; i < N + 1; i++) {
            ispalin[i] = true;
            for(int j = 1; j < i; j++) {
                ispalin[j] = ispalin[j+1] && (s[j-1] == s[i-1]);
            }
            for(int j = 0; j < i; j++) {
                if(ispalin[i-j]) {
                    dp[i] = min(dp[i],dp[i-1-j]+1);
                }
            }
        }
        return dp[N];
    }
};
```
# Explaination: 
The vector ispalin[i] is true if string s[i-1:current char] is palindrom;
The vector dp[i] is the minimum number of cuts from s[0] to s[i-1].

For ispalin, we know a string S with lenth of N is palindrom if 
1. S[0] == S[N-1]
2. S[1] to S[N-2] is a palindrom

So we can get the state transition equation for ispalin[]:
```
 ispalin[j] = ispalin[j+1] && (s[j-1] == s[i-1]);
 ```
 Note the ```ispalin[j+1]``` is updated when i was i-1, it stands for whether s[j:i-1] is palindrom.

For the dp[], we only consider the last cut. If the last string is palindrom, then
```
dp[i] = min(dp[i],dp[i-1-j]+1);
```

 So this question can be solved in O(N) space.

