solutions.content:
Keep track of the minimum number of cuts required to convert a string into subsets of palindrome. Memoize the answer for this substring. Then whenever you recursively reach to this substring just used the memoized value. 
This is an extension of problem [Palindrome Partitioning](https://leetcode.com/problems/palindrome-partitioning/) where you can use the same recursion to generate all palindromic cuts.
```
class Solution:
    def minCut(self, s: str) -> int:
        memo = {}
        def recurse(lst):
            if lst in memo:
                return memo[lst]
            if lst == lst[::-1]:
                return 0
            minn = len(lst)-1
            for i in range(len(lst)):
				# Palindrome check
                if lst[:i+1] == lst[:i+1][::-1]:
                    minn = min(minn, 1 + recurse(lst[i+1:]))
            memo[lst] = minn
            return minn
        return recurse(s)
```

