solutions.content:
The recursion code will defintely will **not** be submitted by LeetCode.
We will memoize it later.
To improve the code after memoization.

The basic thing that comes to notice is to pass the string by reference as length is <= 2000.

**Reason** 
* During pass by value , copy of same is created during function call while recieving the arguments in memory . Copy of integer ,char etc is not costly.
* But for strings , suppose it has 10000 characters then those many numbers of  copies will be created and it will take a large amount of time.
* On the other hand , if you pass by reference then  only the address of that particular block is passed basically the address of the first char, it does'nt create any copy of it,
* No extra time consumption due to creation of copies.

**Recursion Code  plus memoization**
As you can see it is a MCM Variation so the code format is known to you.
Still this solution was giving me TLE as i am making 2 recursive call.
So we can reduce it to one recursion call by just making a small check.

```
class Solution {
public:
    int dp[2001][2001];

    bool is_palindrome(string &s, int start ,int end)
    {
        while(start <end)
        {
            if(s[start] != s[end])
            {
                return false;
            }
            start++;
            end--;
        }
        return true;
    }

    int solve(int i , int j , string &s)
    {
        if(i == j)  // only one element always palindrome 
            return 0; // no cuts

        if(dp[i][j] != -1) // what to say about this
            return dp[i][j];

        if(is_palindrome(s,i,j)) // this is main base condition for func call
