solutions.content:
We check for both odd length and even length palindromes in the given string. 
If a substring is a palindrome, 
: b (aaa) y  -> here (aaa) is a palindrome so , the cuts required for the string  baaa will be similar to that required for the string ba. 

This concept is used, beginning with the maximum value of the cuts required for any string of length n to be n-1 as default.  
(even if the string has no actual palindromee with len>1)

```
class Solution {
public:
    int minCut(string s) {
        int n = s.size();
        vector<int> cut(n,0);  // number of cuts for the first k characters
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++) cut[i]=i;
        for(int c=0; c<n; c++){
            int l=c,r=c; // odd lenth palindrome with center c
            for(;l>=0 && r<n; l--, r++){
                if(s[l]!=s[r]) break;
                if(l==0) cut[r] = 0;
                else cut[r] = min(cut[r], cut[l-1]+1);
            }
            l=c, r=c+1; // even lenth palindrome with center c
            for(;l>=0 && r<n; l--, r++){
                if(s[l]!=s[r]) break;
                if(l==0) cut[r] = 0;
                else cut[r] = min(cut[r], cut[l-1]+1);
            }
        }
        return cut[n-1];
    }
};
```

