The question is a transfromation of PALINDROME PARTITIONING I.

The common point of the 2 questions is they both utilized a boolean matrix** isPalindrome[][]** to query whether a substring of s is Palindrome or not in **O(1) ** time.

The different point of the 2 questions is that instead of using backtracking, we use dp to get the min cut.

For each **s.charAt(i)** in string, it has the following choices: 
1) It is part of a Palindrome which starts at index 0 and ends at i. => 0 cut needed.
2) It is part of a Palindrome which starts at any index **j** in [1, i] and ends at i. => minCut[j - 1] + 1 cut needed.

When doing backtracking/dp problems, always think about **what are the CHOICES** we have in each sub-problem.

Code can be further optimized and I mainly focused on the idea rather than code.

```
class Solution {
    public int minCut(String s) {
        if(s == null || s.length() == 0) {
            return 0;
        }
        int length = s.length();

        boolean[][] isP = new boolean[length][length];
        // populate isP
        populateIsP(s, isP);
        if(isP[0][length - 1]) return 0;

        int[] minCut = new int[length];
        minCut[0] = 0;

        for(int i = 1; i < minCut.length; i++) {
            int curMin = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
            if(isP[0][i]) {
                curMin = 0;
            }
            // j is the start of the merged Palindrome
            for(int j = 1; j <= i; j++) {
               if(isP[j][i]) {
                    curMin = Math.min(curMin, minCut[j - 1] + 1);
                }
            }
            minCut[i] = curMin;
        }
        return minCut[length - 1];
    }

    private void populateIsP(String s, boolean[][] isP) {
        int length = s.length();
        for(int end = 0; end < length; end++) {
            for(int start = 0; start <= end; start++) {
                if(start == end) {
                    isP[start][end] = true;
                } else if(start + 1 == end) {
                    isP[start][end] = s.charAt(start) == s.charAt(end);
                } else {
                    isP[start][end] = s.charAt(start) == s.charAt(end)
                            && isP[start + 1][end - 1];
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
```

